# xtc — Authors and contributors

The xtc project began in 2026 as the runtime substrate for a
threaded PostgreSQL.

## Founding contributors

- Greg Burd <greg@burd.me>

## Acknowledgements

xtc draws ideas from, and ports working code from, several other
open-source projects.  Each port carries the upstream copyright
notice in its source file header.

- The lock manager (`src/ptc/lock/mgr.c`, `dd.c`) takes its lock
  modes, conflict matrix, and deadlock-detection algorithms from
  Berkeley DB (Oracle's BSD-licensed releases).
- The LRLock and LWLock implementations port from
  `~/ws/postgres/lrlck` (PostgreSQL Global Development Group).
- The protothread / Duff's-device coroutine substrate vendors
  Adam Dunkels' `pt.h` (Contiki-OS BSD license).
- The munit test framework is vendored from
  https://github.com/nemequ/munit (MIT license).
- The fiber `make_fcontext` / `jump_fcontext` assembly is
  re-implemented from the Boost.context originals.
- The build apparatus follows the BDB / DBSQL conventions
  authored over decades by Sleepycat Software, Oracle, and the
  DBSQL team.

For a full list of upstream sources, see [`PLAN.md`](../PLAN.md)
section 13.1 and the file headers of the relevant `src/`
modules as they land.
